text: Levytsky is a surname of Ukrainian origin and may refer to * Kost Levytsky, the head of government of the West Ukrainian People's Republic in 1918-19 * Ivan Nechuy-Levytsky, a Ukrainian writer * Mykhailo Levytsky, a metropolitan of Lviv * Mykhailo Vasylyovych Levytsky (diplomat) * Mykhailo Vasylyovych Levytsky (poet) ==See also== * Levitsky, a Russian version * Levitzky, a Jewish version * Lewicki, a Polish version Category:Ukrainian-language surnames
title: Levytsky
